      "slug": "docker-ml-security",
      "titulo": "Hardening Docker Containers for ML Workloads",
      "fecha": "2026-01-10",
      "tags": ["Docker", "MLOps", "Security"],
      "imagen": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1605745341112-85968b19335b?w=800",
      "resumen": "Best practices para securizar contenedores Docker en entornos de Machine Learning con GPU.",
      "contenido": [
        "## Por Qué ML Necesita Atención Especial",
        "",
        "Los contenedores ML tienen requisitos únicos: acceso a GPU, modelos grandes, y a menudo se ejecutan con privilegios elevados. Esto amplía la superficie de ataque.",
        "",
        "## Checklist de Seguridad",
        "",
        "### Base Images",
        "```dockerfile",
        "# MAL: imagen genérica con todo",
        "FROM python:3.11",
        "",
        "# BIEN: imagen slim o distroless",
        "FROM python:3.11-slim-bookworm",
        "```",
        "",
        "### Non-Root User",
        "```dockerfile",
        "RUN useradd -m -u 1000 mluser",
        "USER mluser",
        "```",
        "",
        "### Read-Only Filesystem",
        "```yaml",
        "# docker-compose.yml",
        "services:",
        "  inference:",
        "    read_only: true",
        "    tmpfs:",
        "      - /tmp",
        "```",
        "",
        "### GPU Security",
        "```yaml",
        "deploy:",
        "  resources:",
        "    reservations:",
        "      devices:",
        "        - driver: nvidia",
        "          capabilities: [gpu]",
        "          # Limitar a GPUs específicas",
        "          device_ids: ['0']",
        "```",
        "",
        "## Scanning de Vulnerabilidades",
        "",
        "```bash",
        "# Trivy - el más completo para ML",
        "trivy image mymodel:latest",
        "",
        "# Grype - alternativa rápida",
        "grype mymodel:latest",
        "```",
        "",
        "## Secrets Management",
        "",
        "```dockerfile",
        "# NUNCA hagas esto",
        "ENV OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxx",
        "",
        "# Usa BuildKit secrets",
        "RUN --mount=type=secret,id=api_key cat /run/secrets/api_key",
        "```",
        "",
        "## Conclusión",
        "",
        "Securizar ML containers requiere equilibrar rendimiento y seguridad. Multi-stage builds, usuarios non-root, y scanning continuo son el mínimo."
      ]
    },
